Diagnosis . The species-group is characterized by having yellow or yellowish-red transverse lines, by the presence of a ventral subbasal cluster of spine-like cornuti and a largest diverticulum with (or without) a cluster of spinules in the male vesica, and large bulbous or elliptical appendix bursae with a narrow and heavily sclerotized proximal section in the female genitalia (
Volynkin et al. 2017
).
